Program: Outlook
Title: 22/02/2012
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00nsr9v
Last Broadcast Date: Thu 23 Feb 2012
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, Matthew Bannister talks to former undercover policeman, Mark Kennedy, who became confused about his own identity while infiltrating left wing and environmental protest groups and was accused of "going native". We also hear from Japanese farmer, Naoto Matsumara, who tells us why he's the only person still living inside the exclusion zone around the failed nuclear plant at Fukushima. Show less